The paper deals with the computation of hyperbolic Voronoi diagrams, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the use of these diagrams in designing user interfaces for an image catalog browsing application, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) or information retrieval (cs.IR). However, since the focus of the paper is on the computational geometry aspect, cs.CG is the most likely category. Other possible categories include cs.GR (graphics) since the paper discusses the visualization of hyperbolic Voronoi diagrams, cs.DS (data structures) since the paper discusses the computation of Voronoi diagrams, cs.MG (mathematical software) since the paper presents a computational framework, and cs.SI (social and information networks) since the paper discusses the use of Voronoi diagrams in information retrieval.
